22/05/2007
TIVAT, Montenegro -- The Commander of NATO's Allied Joint Force Command Naples, US Admiral Harry Ulrich, strongly backed ongoing reforms and Montenegro's Euro-Atlantic integration bids, during a meeting with President Filip Vujanovic on Monday (May 21st). 
They met aboard a NATO battle ship, currently in Montenegro's Tivat Bay. 
According to a statement from Vujanovic's office, Ulrich expressed confidence that Montenegrin authorities would continue defence and security reforms and will adopt the necessary legislative framework related to NATO integration. 
(Vijesti - 22/05/07; RTCG - 21/05/07)
